Description: Fragment of neck and shoulder of East Greek pottery closed, vase, probably an amphora; slight ridge at turn of neck; very worn; traces of red-fired glaze on inside of neck; exterior has band of tongues at top of shoulder, the rest worn.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), Well 101 (= Well 5)
Curator's comments: Marked '101' in pencil. Possibly from same vessel as 1965,0930.742
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.008)
